sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.listeners

Class DefaultListeners

  • java.lang.Object
    • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.core.listeners.DefaultListeners

  • public final class DefaultListeners
extends java.lang.Object
    Static accessor methods pertaining to default listener core implementation.

    The core implementation includes default Listener implementation classes along with respective ListenerClassesSupplier as well as default ListenerService, ListenerProvider and ListenerManager.

    The default implementations of listeners as well as listener provider, manager and service are still available by this class even if the respective listeners are unregistered from the core or the services are switched or stopped.

    Note: The core listener implementation currently does not include any default listener implementations, but this is subject to change in the future releases.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell

    • Method Detail

      • getDefaultListenerProvider

        public static final ListenerProvider getDefaultListenerProvider()
        Returns the default listener provider. The returned provider is a standard listener provider constructed using the standard provider builder from ListenerProviders.builder() factory method. Its direct parent and the only predecessor in the listener provider hierarchy is the system listener provider.

        The default listener provider is lazily initialized at the first call of this method.

        Returns:
        the default listener provider
        See Also:
        ListenerProvider, ListenerProviders.builder(), ListenerProviders.getSystemProvider()

      • getDefaultListenerManager

        public static final ListenerManager getDefaultListenerManager()
        Returns the default listener manager. The returned manager is a standard listener manager constructed by the ListenerManagers.create() factory method.

        The default listener manager is lazily initialized at the first call of this method.

        Returns:
        the default listener manager
        See Also:
        ListenerManager, ListenerManagers.create()

      • getDefaultListenerService

        public static final ListenerService getDefaultListenerService()
        Returns the default listener service. The returned service is a standard listener service constructed using the standard service builder from ListenerServices.builder() factory method. It contains the default listener provider and manager.

        The default listener service is lazily initialized at the first call of this method.

        Note: The returned service may be unusable if it has been retrieved by this method earlier and then stopped.

        Returns:
        the default listener service
        See Also:
        ListenerService, ListenerServices.builder(), getDefaultListenerProvider(), getDefaultListenerManager()

      • getDefaultListenerClassesSupplier

        public static final ListenerClassesSupplier getDefaultListenerClassesSupplier()
        Returns the default listener implementation classes supplier. The built supplier dynamically supplies listener implementation classes based on the currently used ListenerProvider obtained by this Services.getListenerService().getListenerProvider() method call at supplying.

        Note: The returned supplier always supplies an empty set because the core listener implementation currently does not include any default listener implementations, but this is subject to change in the future releases.

        Returns:
        the default listener classes supplier
        See Also:
        ListenerClassesSupplier, getDefaultListenerProvider()
